n class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidablePred\">DecidablePred</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#ContinuousMultilinearMap\">ContinuousMultilinearMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#ContinuousMultilinearMap\">ContinuousMultilinearMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"One of the components of the iterated derivative of a continuous multilinear map. Given a\nbijection `e` between a type `α` (typically `Fin k`) and a subset `s` of `ι`, this component is a\ncontinuous multilinear map of `k` vectors `v₁, ..., vₖ`, mapping them\nto `f (x₁, (v_{e.symm 2})₂, x₃, ...)`, where at indices `i` in `s` one uses the `i`-th coordinate of\nthe vector `v_{e.symm i}` and otherwise one uses the `i`-th coordinate of a reference vector `x`.\nThis is continuous multilinear in the components of `x` outside of `s`, and in the `v_j`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#ContinuousMultilinearMap.iteratedFDerivComponent","kind":"def","line":1256,"name":"ContinuousMultilinearMap.iteratedFDerivComponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.lean#L1256-L1281"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#ContinuousLinearEquiv.continuousMultilinearMapCongrLeft_apply\"><span class=\"name\">ContinuousLinearEquiv</span>.<span class=\"name\">continuousMultilinearMapCongrLeft_apply</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ι</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> wE</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E₁</span