=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hC</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>), <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>, <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">m₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m₁</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m₂</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Card.html#Fintype.card\">Fintype.card</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Max.max\">max</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">m₁</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">m₂</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Card.html#Fintype.card\">Fintype.card</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">m₁</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">m₂</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` satisfies a boundedness property around `0`, one can deduce a bound on `f m₁ - f m₂`\nusing the multilinearity. Here, we give a usable but not very precise version. See\n`norm_image_sub_le_of_bound'` for a more precise but less usable version. The bound is\n`‖f m - f m'‖ ≤ C * card ι * ‖m - m'‖ * (max ‖m‖ ‖m'‖) ^ (card ι - 1)`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#MultilinearMap.norm_image_sub_le_of_bound","kind":"theorem","line":247,"name":"MultilinearMap.norm_image_sub_le_of_bound","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Anal