fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>), <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>, <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">m₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m₁</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m₂</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">∑ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>, <span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>, <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">if</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">then</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">else</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Max.max\">max</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If a multilinear map `f` satisfies a boundedness property around `0`,\none can deduce a bound on `f m₁ - f m₂` using the multilinearity.\nHere, we give a precise but hard to use version.\nSee `norm_image_sub_le_of_bound` for a less precise but more usable version.\nThe bound reads\n`‖f m - f m'‖ ≤\n  C * ‖m 1 - m' 1‖ * max ‖m 2‖ ‖m' 2‖ * max ‖m 3‖ ‖m' 3‖ * ... * max ‖m n‖ ‖m' n‖ + ...`,\nwhere the other terms in the sum are the same products where `1` is replaced by any `i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#MultilinearMap.norm_image_sub_le_of_bound'","kind":"theorem","line":201,"name":"MultilinearMap.norm_image_sub_le_of_bound'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.lean#L201-L245"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#MultilinearMap.exists_