roup/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>, <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If a continuous multilinear map in finitely many variables on normed spaces satisfies\nthe inequality `‖f m‖ ≤ C * ∏ i, ‖m i‖` on a shell `ε i / ‖c i‖ < ‖m i‖ < ε i` for some positive\nnumbers `ε i` and elements `c i : 𝕜`, `1 < ‖c i‖`, then it satisfies this inequality for all `m`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#MultilinearMap.bound_of_shell_of_continuous","kind":"theorem","line":171,"name":"MultilinearMap.bound_of_shell_of_continuous","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.lean#L171-L178"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Multilinear/Basic.html#MultilinearMap.bound_of_shell_of_norm_map_coord_zero\"><span class=\"name\"